==English==

===Etymology===
19th Century, from [[Italian]] ''[[irredentista]]'', from ''[[ir]]''- ([[in]]) + ''[[redento]]'' ([[redeemed]]), from [[Latin]] ''[[redemptus]]'' (bought back); see [[redeem]].

===Pronunciation===

*[[IPA]]: (,ɪrɪ'dɛntɪst)

===Noun===
(''plural:''irredentists)

# A person, especially a member of 19th-Century Italian association, who favours the acquisition of territory that was once part of his country or is considered to have been.

===Adjective===
'''irredentist'''

# Of or relating to irredentists or their policies.

